name: Middlesex Community College
directions: Founder's Hall Building. The lay out of the building is a circle shape. Once you get through the front door area, take a right and go around the circle until you see the public bathrooms. There are a men's and a women's bathroom, but past these on the left is a single bathroom that is unisex/handicapped. It is across the hallway from the Career/Counseling Offices. Parking in the lower parking lot is most convenient.
comment: Don't worry about being a student. I doubt anyone would notice if you weren't. It is a public school.
